1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:00,280 --> 00:00:01,880
(Previously)
Not everyone's on your side.

3
00:00:02,680 --> 00:00:03,920
Someone wants to see you fall.

4
00:00:04,360 --> 00:00:07,040
Don't tell me
Raffy knows about Arnold and me.

5
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:10,200
Can you help me?

6
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:13,040
If you help me this time,
you'll be saving everyone.

7
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:14,360
You dropped your phone.

8
00:00:14,920 --> 00:00:15,920
Explain it.

9
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,560
Tell me you didn't take me out
just to delete Dean's video.

10
00:00:18,680 --> 00:00:20,160
Will you stop doing things for Jack?

11
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:21,840
The one who likes you is right here.

12
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:24,000
Someone like you… is not for me.

13
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:26,680
Happy three-year anniversary.

14
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:28,120
Will you marry me?

15
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:30,720
Is this the time to joke around?

16
00:00:31,160 --> 00:00:33,400
If we're still together in the future…

17
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:34,640
I'd want to get married.

18
00:00:34,920 --> 00:00:38,400
Now it's clear to you
how we feel about each other.

19
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:40,280
I like you as more than just a friend, Tua.

20
00:00:40,760 --> 00:00:41,760
Will you be my boyfriend?

21
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:48,800
(Episode 9: The Climax)

22
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:11,320
When will I ever be in your line of sight?

23
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:13,000
When will you see my worth?

24
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:15,480
Someone like you… is not for me.

25
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:23,240
On days you miss me,
you can play my playlists.

26
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:07,000
"Only Friends : Dream On"

27
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:27,640
Sorry, guys. Didn't mean to interrupt.

28
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,800
Congratulations, Tua.

29
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,440
So, are you two dating?

30
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,760
If I know, I'll know how to act.

31
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,760
You guys saw it earlier.

32
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,200
Take good care of Tua.

33
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:56,800
Don't make him angry.

34
00:04:57,440 --> 00:05:00,320
There was this one time
Dean wore his clothes without asking.

35
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:02,440
He got furious. It was freaking scary.

36
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:05,320
Mm.

37
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:06,920
Don't worry.

38
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:09,760
I've been taking good
care of him all along.

39
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,520
Right, Mr. Tua? Hm?

40
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:14,280
Right?

41
00:05:14,640 --> 00:05:15,640
Stop it.

42
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,040
Hello. What's up?

43
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:33,440
Right now?

44
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,880
Okay. I'll be right there.

45
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:43,040
Hey, Raffy called. He said it's urgent.

46
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:44,920
I'm going to see him.

47
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:47,320
See you.

48
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,160
It's probably nothing.

49
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:19,320
What is it?

50
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:26,440
I…

51
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:29,320
I have something important to tell you.

52
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:33,680
Uh-huh.

53
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,720
Just don't be shocked.

54
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:39,280
Okay.

55
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:41,720
I…

56
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:47,720
I want to drop out of the play.

57
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,040
Why?

58
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:51,720
What happened?

59
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,040
I don't think the play needs me.

60
00:06:56,880 --> 00:07:00,200
People want to see Dean and Arnold
more than Arnold and me.

61
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:04,880
I think the sponsor will understand.

62
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:09,880
I get that, but the show
starts in a few days.

63
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,120
And you've been rehearsing for so long.

64
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:13,960
I don't want you to regret it later.

65
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:18,560
Don't worry about me.
I've thought it through.

66
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,200
I'd rather work behind the scenes.

67
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,200
Raffy.

68
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:30,040
Am I putting too much
pressure on you during rehearsals?

69
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,440
It's not that, Jack.

70
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:36,760
Is it about Dean?

71
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:47,320
A little.

72
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,480
But that's not all.

73
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,880
I've also lost my passion for acting.

74
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:57,160
I just realized I don't want to
be an actor for the rest of my life.

75
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:04,720
Anyway, thank you so much
for giving me this opportunity.

76
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:10,480
Gosh, okay.

77
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:17,680
If you've thought it through,
then I respect your decision.

78
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:30,760
That's nice.

79
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:34,000
It's awesome, actually.

80
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:41,040
Why are you here?

81
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:46,880
I'm just… tired of the same old playlists.

82
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:48,920
I want to hear you play live.

83
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:03,400
Want to grab some
congee with me after work?

84
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:07,840
What's this about?

85
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,600
I just want to talk to you.

86
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:16,280
What? Jack didn't want you?

87
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,600
So you came to me?

88
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:21,680
It's not that he didn't want me.
I chose this myself.

89
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:27,560
I don't get it. Why did you quit the play?

90
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,840
You fought so hard to get that role.

91
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:36,040
I… just lost my passion.

92
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,400
Lost your passion?

93
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,840
See? This is what happens
when you've been spoiled your whole life.

94
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:44,560
You do whatever you want,
and the moment you don't, you just quit.

95
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,520
Are you done lecturing me?

96
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:50,400
Are you eating with me or not? I'm hungry.

97
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:51,600
I'll wait.

98
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:21,280
MR. DUI'S À LA CARTE &amp; CONGEE SET

99
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:27,600
Wow. This is new to me.

100
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:31,320
I thought you only ate
fancy food catered to rich kids.

101
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:35,680
Pickled plum soup and salted egg salad
are my favorites in the whole world.

102
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:38,360
Try them.
They're what this place is known for.

103
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:42,680
Just try.

104
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:44,800
Here.

105
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:47,880
You have to eat them together.

106
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:49,720
Like this.

107
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,560
Put this on top.

108
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,000
So good.

109
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:09,040
Mm. It's good.

110
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:11,400
See? I told you it's good.

111
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:13,920
I only bring people
I'm really close to here.

112
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:16,160
I don't share this place with just anyone.

113
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:33,320
This is their best dish, stir-fried
Chinese black olives with minced pork.

114
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:36,800
Try it.

115
00:11:38,920 --> 00:11:39,920
You don't believe me?

116
00:11:40,040 --> 00:11:41,040
Here.

117
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:03,440
So you asked me out just to eat?

118
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:05,120
Nothing else?

119
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:07,840
Mm.

120
00:12:08,040 --> 00:12:09,040
Why?

121
00:12:10,680 --> 00:12:11,680
Nothing.

122
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:14,400
It's just every time I see you,
there's always trouble.

123
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,120
I just wanted to have a peaceful meal,

124
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:18,600
but I didn't want to
come alone, so I asked you.

125
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,840
Besides, I don't want to go home yet.

126
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,160
Here she is.

127
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,360
Calling at the perfect time.

128
00:12:37,102 --> 00:12:38,400
You're not gonna pick up?

129
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:39,080
No.

130
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:41,520
I'm in a no-contact phase
with my mom right now.

131
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:50,840
Hey, why aren't you eating?

132
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:53,600
You don't usually eat rice porridge?

133
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:57,480
I don't?

134
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:01,600
I'd say I eat it more than you do.

135
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:04,640
Look.

136
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:09,880
Then eat more.

137
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:12,680
The salted egg is a must.

138
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:15,760
Here. Eat it all together.

139
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:20,400
Thanks, though, for sharing
your favorite place with me.

140
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:35,760
He's kind of different today.

141
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,640
I couldn't bring myself to be mad at him.

142
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:42,200
With him, it actually feels nice and easy.

143
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:58,520
Whoo!

144
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:17,040
Three, two, one.

145
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:21,600
Argh!

146
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,960
Argh!

147
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,560
Argh!

148
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:31,360
Argh!

149
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:48,800
You okay?

150
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,920
A big guy like you
can't even handle that ride?

151
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:03,840
I just didn't get enough sleep.
I worked at Pink's until late last night.

152
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:04,760
Ah.

153
00:15:04,761 --> 00:15:06,041
It won't be like this next time.

154
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:09,360
All right. We'll see about that.

155
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:20,800
It's all an act.

156
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:29,560
Have some water.

157
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:41,480
This place reminds me of when I was a kid.

158
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:45,800
My mom used to bring me here.
I still have the photo.

159
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:51,200
Who would've thought I'd end up
dating the amusement park owner's son?

160
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:58,520
Who knows? Maybe we met here
when we were kids.

161
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:02,400
Let me tell you. If you're in
that photo, I'll believe in destiny.

162
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:06,720
We passed by each other as kids,
and ended up falling in love as adults.

163
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:15,320
Ever since we leveled up our relationship,
you've been a lot sweeter.

164
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:21,120
Tua, son.

165
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:22,240
Hey, Dad.

166
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:23,720
Hi.

167
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:27,320
You don't come home much these days.

168
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:30,400
Because Jack works your son to the bone.

169
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:32,160
The play's about to open, Dad.

170
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:34,000
That's college life.

171
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:35,440
Have all the fun you can.

172
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:39,200
But after the play, you'll have to
help me design a new mascot costume.

173
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:41,280
Of course, Dad.

174
00:16:47,920 --> 00:16:49,600
This is Arnold.

175
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:51,120
Hello, sir.

176
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:53,840
Your friend?

177
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:58,120
Not my friend, Dad.

178
00:16:58,800 --> 00:16:59,440
My boyfriend.

179
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:01,320
What? Seriously?

180
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,840
This is the first guy
you've brought to meet me.

181
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:08,960
I'm getting flustered.

182
00:17:09,320 --> 00:17:11,440
It's my first time bringing
my partner to meet my dad.

183
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:16,160
Actually, we only recently
went from friends to boyfriends, sir.

184
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:18,840
Take good care of my son.

185
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,160
Yes, sir.

186
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:24,920
Because if you don't
or you break his heart,

187
00:17:25,840 --> 00:17:28,320
you might find yourself stuck on a ride.

188
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:31,400
And I'll lock you in the haunted house.

189
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,200
I'm kidding.

190
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:41,240
Come on, Dad.

191
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:44,160
Have fun. I'll get back to work.

192
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:44,920
All right.

193
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:46,360
Goodbye, sir.

194
00:17:51,360 --> 00:17:52,360
Watch your back.

195
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:04,880
Hey.

196
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:08,280
Are you implying something
by asking me to watch this with you?

197
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:12,080
No, I just like this movie.

198
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:14,920
But I don't want us to end up like that.

199
00:18:28,120 --> 00:18:29,120
So…

200
00:18:29,840 --> 00:18:33,320
When you talked to Raffy the other day,
is that really all he said?

201
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:35,760
Mm.

202
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:36,920
He wanted to quit.

203
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:39,840
Why?

204
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:41,800
What do you think he said to me?

205
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:51,560
I thought he was scared of being compared,
since I'm a better actor than him.

206
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:54,960
It'd be embarrassing
for him to keep going with the role.

207
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:59,400
But don't worry.
I'll do my best with this role for you.

208
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:02,040
Sure.

209
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:04,240
No one's better than you.

210
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:11,320
Hey, Jack.

211
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:13,440
Looks like there's an activity
before the movie.

212
00:19:13,640 --> 00:19:14,640
Should we check it out?

213
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:16,280
Let's go.

214
00:19:19,080 --> 00:19:24,640
Before we start the movie, let's see
who here is a true romantic movie nerd.

215
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:26,799
Complete these famous lines
and name the movies.

216
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:30,080
Whoever gets the most
correct answers wins this Oscar.

217
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:33,600
I want that Oscar.

218
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:36,520
It's fake.

219
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:39,200
Fake or not, I still want it.

220
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:42,640
First one. Super easy.
Raise your hand if you know it.

221
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:46,119
"Call me by…"

222
00:19:46,120 --> 00:19:46,560
Yes?

223
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:49,439
"Call me by your name,
and I'll call you by mine."

224
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:50,600
From Call Me by Your Name.

225
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:51,640
That's correct!

226
00:19:51,641 --> 00:19:54,120
Wow, he was so fast
I didn't even finish the line.

227
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:55,240
Very good.

228
00:19:55,241 --> 00:19:57,520
Next one.

229
00:19:58,160 --> 00:20:01,720
"I'm just a girl, standing
in front of a boy…"

230
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:02,720
Yes?

231
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:05,360
"Asking him to love her."
From Notting Hill.

232
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:06,720
That's correct.

233
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:09,680
Ah! Another strong contender.

234
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:11,440
Next one.

235
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:14,920
"Shone, I have something to tell you."

236
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:18,720
"I really like you.
I've liked you for three years."

237
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:21,600
"I did everything I could
to change myself for you."

238
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:24,040
"I joined the traditional dance club,
acted in a play,

239
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:27,080
became a drum major,
and studied harder, all because of you."

240
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:33,160
"But now I realize what I should've done
from the start was tell you that…"

241
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:34,440
"I like you, Shone."

242
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,040
From Crazy Little Thing Called Love.

243
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:38,799
Very impressive!

244
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:42,280
Wow! He almost quoted the whole movie.

245
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:46,680
He quoted every word. That's amazing.

246
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:49,200
How do you remember all that?

247
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:51,600
I used that monologue
to pass the faculty entrance exam.

248
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:53,480
And now, the final one.

249
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,920
It's a classic.

250
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:59,920
"What light through yonder window breaks?"

251
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:02,440
Does anyone know this one?

252
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:03,800
Anyone?

253
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:07,240
Yes?

254
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:09,880
"It is the east, and Juliet is the sun."

255
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:11,320
From Romeo and Juliet.

256
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:12,600
That's correct.

257
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:16,600
We have a winner, everyone.

258
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:20,400
Here's your Oscar.

259
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:03,280
Hello. What's up, Dao?
I'm watching a movie.

260
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:05,360
(Dean, help me.)

261
00:22:05,361 --> 00:22:07,080
(Can you come to my place right now?)

262
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:10,320
Okay. Calm down. I'll be right there.

263
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:38,280
Open the door.

264
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:39,680
Hey! Open up!

265
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,479
Or we're calling the police.

266
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:42,320
Open the damn door!

267
00:22:42,321 --> 00:22:43,840
Dean, help me!

268
00:22:44,240 --> 00:22:45,240
What?!

269
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:47,040
Dao!

270
